INSERT INTO "mail_templates"("hashtag","lang","subject","description","contents")
VALUES
(E'#NewUserParallelSubmissionAllowed',E'default',E'{{appName}}: Welcome as a new user',E'Mail to user to acknowledge his/her registration in PCI allowing parallel submission',E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have recently joined {{appLongName}}. Thank you for your interest and for registering with us.</p>\n<p>More information about {{appName}} can be found here <a href="{{baseurl}}">{{baseurl}}</a> and in this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4PZhpnc8wwo">video</a>.</p>\n<p>As a user, you can submit your preprints to {{appName}} for evaluation and recommendation - and find five good reasons to do so in this short <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jMhVl__gupg">video</a>. Briefly, your preprints must first be deposited on a preprint server, such as bioRxiv, and you must choose between A) exclusive submission to {{appName}}, or B) parallel submission with journals. Please go to <a href="{{infourl}}">{{infourl}}</a> for more information on these options.</p>\n<p>When submitting your preprints, you are allowed to suggest recommenders. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews. A preprint recommended by {{appLongName}} is an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\n<p>Once you have submitted your preprint, one of the recommenders you suggest, or any other recommenders from the community may express an interest in initiating the evaluation process for your preprint, which will involve sending your preprint out for peer review.</p>\n<p>If you wish to submit a preprint, please click on the "Submit a preprint" button on the home page of the {{appName}} website.</p>\n<p>As a user, you will also receive alerts every {{days}} concerning recommendations in the following fields published on the {{appLongName}} web site: {{thematics}}.</p>\n<p>Finally, if you are interested in becoming a recommender for {{appName}} - <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2BDrPoHGkn0">see video</a> - please contact a current recommender in your field via this link <a href="{{recommurl}}">{{recommurl}}</a>.</p>\n<p>Thanks again for your interest and for joining {{appLongName}}.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appLongName}}</p>'),
(E'#SubmitterParallelPreprintUnderConsideration',E'default',E'{{appName}}: Consideration of your preprint',E'Mail to submitter that a recommender took his/her preprint in charge in case of parallel submission',E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}. We are pleased to inform you that a {{appName}} recommender has initiated the evaluation process.</p>\n<p>At this stage of the process, your article will be sent to several referees, to ensure that at least two high-quality reviews are obtained. Based on this review, the recommender will reject, recommend or ask you to modify your article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers. The mean time to this first decision is about {{recomm_limit_days}} days.</p>\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. If recommended by {{appName}}, your preprint will become an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage of the procedure.</p>\n<p>You have selected the option of submitting elsewhere in parallel. We encourage you to finish the peer-review process with {{appName}} even if your manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere. Please note that if this does happen and you abandon the process with {{appName}} after reviewers have contributed their time toward evaluation, we will post the reviewers\' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers\' work and in order to enable critical discussion. If you do not agree with this, please consider cancelling your submission now, before reviewers are recruited.</p>\n<p>To view your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to \'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints\' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>'),
(E'#SubmitterParallelPreprintSubmitted',E'default',E'{{appName}}: Submission of your preprint',E'Mail to submitter to indicate the validation of his/her submission in case of parallel submission',E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>Thank you for submitting your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong>, to {{appDescription}} ({{appName}}).</p>\n<p>If you have not already done so, you can suggest recommenders who could initiate the evaluation of your preprint. A recommender is very similar to a journal editor (responsible for finding reviewers, collecting reviews, and making editorial decisions based on reviews), and may eventually recommend your preprint after one or several rounds of reviews.</p>\n<p>Please remember that {{appName}} is under no obligation to consider your preprint. We cannot guarantee that your preprint will be reviewed, but all possible efforts will be made to make this possible. You will be notified by e-mail if a {{appName}} recommender decides to start the peer-review process for your preprint.</p>\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. If recommended by {{appName}}, your preprint will become an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage of the procedure.</p>\n<p>You have selected the option of submitting elsewhere in parallel. We encourage you to finish the peer-review process with {{appName}} even if your manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere. Please note that if this does happen and you abandon the process with {{appName}} after reviewers have contributed their time toward evaluation, we will post the reviewers\' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers\' work and in order to enable critical discussion. If you do not agree with this, please consider cancelling your submission now, before reviewers are recruited.</p>\n<p>To view your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to \'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints\' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>'),
