(E'#SubmitterParallelPreprintUnderConsiderationStage2',E'default',E'{{appName}}: Consideration of your preprint',E'Mail to submitter that a recommender took his/her preprint in charge in case of parallel submission',E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have submitted your preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> to {{appName}}. We are pleased to inform you that a {{appName}} recommender has initiated the evaluation process.</p>\n<p>At this stage of the process, your article will be sent to several referees, to ensure that at least two high-quality reviews are obtained. Based on this review, the recommender will reject, recommend or ask you to modify your article and to respond to the questions and points raised by the reviewers. The mean time to this first decision is about {{recomm_limit_days}} days.</p>\n<p>If after one or several rounds of reviews, the recommender handling your preprint reaches a favorable conclusion, all the editorial correspondence (reviews, recommender’s decisions, authors’ replies) and a recommendation text will be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. If recommended by {{appName}}, your preprint will become an article that may be used and cited like any ‘classic’ article published in a peer-reviewed journal.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, if the recommender decides not to recommend your article, the reviews and the decision will be sent to you, but they will not be published or publicly released by {{appName}}. They will be safely stored in our database, to which only the Managing Board has access. You will be notified by e-mail at each stage of the procedure.</p>\n<p>You have selected the option of submitting elsewhere in parallel. We encourage you to finish the peer-review process with {{appName}} even if your manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere. Please note that if this does happen and you abandon the process with {{appName}} after reviewers have contributed their time toward evaluation, we will post the reviewers\' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers\' work and in order to enable critical discussion. If you do not agree with this, please consider cancelling your submission now, before reviewers are recruited.</p>\n<p>To view your submission, please follow this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a> or log onto the {{appName}} website and go to \'For contributors —&gt; Your submitted preprints\' in the top menu.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for your submission.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>'),
(E'#RecommenderThankForPreprintParallelSubmission',E'default',E'{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of a preprint',E'Mail to recommender to thanks him/her for taking a preprint in charge in case of parallel submission',E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\n<p><strong>We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this preprint within the next 24 h</strong>, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this preprint within {{reviewLimitText}}. We thank you in advance for respecting this commitment.</p>\n<p>Invitations to review can be sent using this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. You can also log on to the {{appName}} website and go to \'For recommenders&nbsp;—&gt; Preprints you are handling\' in the top menu, and click on the \'choose a reviewer\' button.</p>\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors\' replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>The authors have chosen to submit elsewhere in parallel. As there is a chance that the manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere and consequently the authors might abandon the process at {{appName}}, we have the following mechanism to ensure reviewers’ work is respected and documented. If the authors abandon the process at {{appName}} after reviewers have written their reports, you should post the reviewers\' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers\' work and in order to enable critical discussion. Note that there remains the outcome of rejection by you, wherein reports are not made public.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>'),
(E'#RecommenderThankForPreprintParallelSubmissionStage1',E'default',E'{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of a preprint',E'Mail to recommender to thanks him/her for taking a preprint in charge in case of parallel submission',E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\n<p><strong>We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this preprint within the next 24 h</strong>, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this preprint within {{reviewLimitText}}. We thank you in advance for respecting this commitment.</p>\n<p>Invitations to review can be sent using this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. You can also log on to the {{appName}} website and go to \'For recommenders&nbsp;—&gt; Preprints you are handling\' in the top menu, and click on the \'choose a reviewer\' button.</p>\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors\' replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>The authors have chosen to submit elsewhere in parallel. As there is a chance that the manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere and consequently the authors might abandon the process at {{appName}}, we have the following mechanism to ensure reviewers’ work is respected and documented. If the authors abandon the process at {{appName}} after reviewers have written their reports, you should post the reviewers\' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers\' work and in order to enable critical discussion. Note that there remains the outcome of rejection by you, wherein reports are not made public.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>'),
(E'#RecommenderThankForPreprintParallelSubmissionStage2',E'default',E'{{appName}}: Thank you for handling the evaluation of a preprint',E'Mail to recommender to thanks him/her for taking a preprint in charge in case of parallel submission',E'<p>Dear {{destPerson}},</p>\n<p>You have agreed to be the recommender handling the preprint entitled <strong>{{articleTitle}}</strong> by {{articleAuthors}} (DOI <a href="{{articleDoi}}">{{articleDoi}}</a>). Thank you very much for your contribution.</p>\n<p><strong>We remind you that you have agreed to send out 5-10 invitations to review this preprint within the next 24 h</strong>, and to send out reminders and/or new invitations, over a period of one week if necessary, until you find at least two reviewers willing to review this preprint within {{reviewLimitText}}. We thank you in advance for respecting this commitment.</p>\n<p>Invitations to review can be sent using this link <a href="{{linkTarget}}">{{linkTarget}}</a>. You can also log on to the {{appName}} website and go to \'For recommenders&nbsp;—&gt; Preprints you are handling\' in the top menu, and click on the \'choose a reviewer\' button.</p>\n<p>The reviews you receive should guide your decision – <strong>within 10 days of receiving the last review</strong> – as to whether to ‘Revise’, ‘Recommend’ or ‘Reject’ the preprint.</p>\n<p>If your decision is to ‘Recommend’ this preprint, you will need to write a “recommendation”, which will have its own DOI and be published by {{appName}} under the license CC-BY-ND. The recommendation is a short article, similar to a News &amp; Views piece. It has its own title, contains between about 300 and 1500 words, describes the context and explains why the preprint is particularly interesting. The limitations of the preprint can also be discussed. This text also contains references (citing, at least, the preprint being recommended). All editorial correspondence (reviews, your decisions, authors\' replies) relating to the preprint will also be published by {{appName}}.</p>\n<p>The authors have chosen to submit elsewhere in parallel. As there is a chance that the manuscript is accepted for publication elsewhere and consequently the authors might abandon the process at {{appName}}, we have the following mechanism to ensure reviewers’ work is respected and documented. If the authors abandon the process at {{appName}} after reviewers have written their reports, you should post the reviewers\' reports on the {{appName}} website as recognition of the reviewers\' work and in order to enable critical discussion. Note that there remains the outcome of rejection by you, wherein reports are not made public.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you need assistance in any way do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>We thank you again for initiating and managing this evaluation.</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p>The Managing Board of {{appName}}</p>');
